{% block body %}
<div class="title">
    <img src="{{ absolute_url(asset('build/icons/486.svg')) }}" width="32" height="32" alt="cpu">
    CPU search guide
</div>
<div class="search-help-container">The search page is comprised out of three types of fields:
{% apply markdown_to_html %}
- text fields
- dynamic select fields
    * up to 100 items will be rendered in the list at once
    * if more than 100 items exist in the list they will remain hidden until you start typing, at which point the list is instantly filtered and updated with the remaining entries
- widgets with dynamic select fields
    * you can add and remove select fields using the [![add](/build/icons/add.svg) Add] and [![del](/build/icons/delete.svg) Delete] buttons, respectively.
    * the select fields work in the same way as described above
{% endapply %}
</div>
<div class="search-help-container">In the CPU search page, you will have a few filters which you can apply:
{% apply markdown_to_html %}
- Manufacturer
    * if selected, it will match all the CPUs with that manufacturer
- Name
    * if filled, it matches all CPUs with that name
    * DOES NOT match the manufacturer!
- CPU frequency
    * if selected, it will match all CPUs with that speed
- Bus speed
    * if selected, it will match all CPUs with that bus speed

### Note on widgets: a maximum of 6 widgets can be added, due to query complexity constraints, each widget acts like a logical AND for your search filters.
- Sockets
    * if added, it will match all the CPUs which contain that socket
- Families
    * if added, it will match all the CPUs which contain that CPU family
{% endapply %}
</div>
{% endblock %}
